<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="385" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.413 M28/10.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 722.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of the Department’s instruction No. 238 of the 19th instant,
                            enclosing a letter addressed to the Minister of Foreign Affairs
                            (Secretary of State) of Cuba, acknowledging a telegram sent by him in
                            regard to the reception accorded the Cuban representatives to the Maine
                            memorial ceremonies; and to report that I have transmitted the letter in
                            question to Mr. Torriente.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hugh S. Gibson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>